    <text id="B0217T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Terry, the clerk in Winchester, returns an expense to Jackson for correction.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau <abbr expan="Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned">R. F. &amp; A.</abbr>
                    Lands<lb/>Head <abbr expan="Quarters">Qrs</abbr> 9<hi rend="super">t</hi> Sub
                    <abbr expan="District">Dist.</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr>
                    <name type="recipient">Mr. <abbr expan="Thomas">Thos.</abbr> P.
                        Jackson<lb/>Agent<lb/>Staunton, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1867-10-26"><abbr expan="October">Oct.</abbr> 26th 1867</date>
                        <name type="place">Winchester, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I return herewith for correction your accounts for expenses incurred in
                    manufacture of Furniture for Schoolhouse at Staunton. The letter from this
                    office authorizing the expenditure, expressly stated it was to be for "Desks."</p>

                <p>I again request that when blanks are sent you for extraordinary expenditures, of
                    this kind, you will return them receipted in blank and the memorandum of
                    articles purchased or services rendered, sent on a separate sheet of paper, to
                    avoid the trouble, delay &amp; expense of their return for correction.</p>

                <p>Please return the new set of forms which are inclosed, without delay.</p>

                <pb n="2"/>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very Respectfully<lb/>Your <abbr expan="Obedient">Obedt</abbr>
                        Servant<lb/>In the absence of <abbr expan="Captain">Capt.</abbr> John A.
                        McDonnell, <abbr expan="Sub Assistant Commissioner">Sub. Asst. Comr</abbr></salute>
                    <signed>A. F. Terry<lb/>Clerk</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
